{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":843,"text":"In 2007, I became the attorney general"},{"time":3434,"text":"of the state of New Jersey."},{"time":5159,"text":"Before that, I'd been a criminal prosecutor,"},{"time":7439,"text":"first in the Manhattan district attorney's office,"},{"time":10120,"text":"and then at the United States Department of Justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12770,"text":"But when I became the attorney general,"},{"time":14971,"text":"two things happened that changed \nthe way I see criminal justice."},{"time":18866,"text":"The first is that I asked what I thought"},{"time":20896,"text":"were really basic questions."},{"time":23082,"text":"I wanted to understand who we were arresting,"},{"time":25938,"text":"who we were charging,"},{"time":27602,"text":"and who we were putting in our nation's jails"},{"time":29730,"text":"and prisons."},{"time":31146,"text":"I also wanted to understand"},{"time":32794,"text":"if we were making decisions"},{"time":34123,"text":"in a way that made us safer."},{"time":36641,"text":"And I couldn't get this information out."},{"time":39893,"text":"It turned out that most big criminal justice agencies"},{"time":43250,"text":"like my own"},{"time":44552,"text":"didn't track the things that matter."},{"time":46934,"text":"So after about a month of being incredibly frustrated,"},{"time":50252,"text":"I walked down into a conference room"},{"time":52223,"text":"that was filled with detectives"},{"time":54113,"text":"and stacks and stacks of case files,"},{"time":56895,"text":"and the detectives were sitting there"},{"time":58071,"text":"with yellow legal pads taking notes."},{"time":60305,"text":"They were trying to get the information"},{"time":61891,"text":"I was looking for"},{"time":63109,"text":"by going through case by case"},{"time":65154,"text":"for the past five years."},{"time":67052,"text":"And as you can imagine,"},{"time":68705,"text":"when we finally got the results, they weren't good."},{"time":71348,"text":"It turned out that we were doing"},{"time":73003,"text":"a lot of low-level drug cases"},{"time":75023,"text":"on the streets just around the corner"},{"time":76498,"text":"from our office in Trenton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78766,"text":"The second thing that happened"},{"time":80233,"text":"is that I spent the day in the Camden,\nNew Jersey police department."},{"time":83907,"text":"Now, at that time, Camden, New Jersey,"},{"time":85794,"text":"was the most dangerous city in America."},{"time":88446,"text":"I ran the Camden Police\nDepartment because of that."},{"time":92273,"text":"I spent the day in the police department,"},{"time":94385,"text":"and I was taken into a room\nwith senior police officials,"},{"time":97111,"text":"all of whom were working hard"},{"time":98786,"text":"and trying very hard to reduce crime in Camden."},{"time":102043,"text":"And what I saw in that room,"},{"time":103869,"text":"as we talked about how to reduce crime,"},{"time":106114,"text":"were a series of officers with a\nlot of little yellow sticky notes."},{"time":109973,"text":"And they would take a yellow sticky\nand they would write something on it"},{"time":112823,"text":"and they would put it up on a board."},{"time":114622,"text":"And one of them said, \n\"We had a robbery two weeks ago."},{"time":116793,"text":"We have no suspects.\""},{"time":118504,"text":"And another said, \"We had a shooting in this neighborhood last week. We have no suspects.\""},{"time":123531,"text":"We weren't using data-driven policing."},{"time":126114,"text":"We were essentially trying to fight crime"},{"time":128156,"text":"with yellow Post-it notes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130683,"text":"Now, both of these things made me realize"},{"time":132818,"text":"fundamentally that we were failing."},{"time":136069,"text":"We didn't even know who was\nin our criminal justice system,"},{"time":139192,"text":"we didn't have any data about\nthe things that mattered,"},{"time":142427,"text":"and we didn't share data or use analytics"},{"time":144995,"text":"or tools to help us make better decisions"},{"time":147146,"text":"and to reduce crime."},{"time":149149,"text":"And for the first time, I started to think"},{"time":151373,"text":"about how we made decisions."},{"time":153283,"text":"When I was an assistant D.A.,"},{"time":154680,"text":"and when I was a federal prosecutor,"},{"time":156550,"text":"I looked at the cases in front of me,"},{"time":158296,"text":"and I generally made decisions based on my instinct"},{"time":160922,"text":"and my experience."},{"time":162614,"text":"When I became attorney general,"},{"time":164273,"text":"I could look at the system as a whole,"},{"time":165912,"text":"and what surprised me is that I found"},{"time":167730,"text":"that that was exactly how we were doing it"},{"time":169635,"text":"across the entire system --"},{"time":171938,"text":"in police departments, in prosecutors's offices,"},{"time":174339,"text":"in courts and in jails."},{"time":177139,"text":"And what I learned very quickly"},{"time":179336,"text":"is that we weren't doing a good job."},{"time":182969,"text":"So I wanted to do things differently."},{"time":184985,"text":"I wanted to introduce data and analytics"},{"time":187182,"text":"and rigorous statistical analysis"},{"time":189231,"text":"into our work."},{"time":190631,"text":"In short, I wanted to moneyball criminal justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193601,"text":"Now, moneyball, as many of you know,"},{"time":195628,"text":"is what the Oakland A's did,"},{"time":197197,"text":"where they used smart data and statistics"},{"time":199170,"text":"to figure out how to pick players"},{"time":200792,"text":"that would help them win games,"},{"time":202313,"text":"and they went from a system that \nwas based on baseball scouts"},{"time":205293,"text":"who used to go out and watch players"},{"time":207153,"text":"and use their instinct and experience,"},{"time":208790,"text":"the scouts' instincts and experience,"},{"time":210533,"text":"to pick players, from one to use"},{"time":212246,"text":"smart data and rigorous statistical analysis"},{"time":215068,"text":"to figure out how to pick players\nthat would help them win games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218439,"text":"It worked for the Oakland A's,"},{"time":220237,"text":"and it worked in the state of New Jersey."},{"time":222456,"text":"We took Camden off the top of the list"},{"time":224529,"text":"as the most dangerous city in America."},{"time":226700,"text":"We reduced murders there by 41 percent,"},{"time":229855,"text":"which actually means 37 lives were saved."},{"time":232837,"text":"And we reduced all crime in the city by 26 percent."},{"time":236577,"text":"We also changed the way\nwe did criminal prosecutions."},{"time":239816,"text":"So we went from doing low-level drug crimes"},{"time":241821,"text":"that were outside our building"},{"time":243463,"text":"to doing cases of statewide importance,"},{"time":245805,"text":"on things like reducing violence\nwith the most violent offenders,"},{"time":248963,"text":"prosecuting street gangs,"},{"time":250821,"text":"gun and drug trafficking, and political corruption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254229,"text":"And all of this matters greatly,"},{"time":256731,"text":"because public safety to me"},{"time":258676,"text":"is the most important function of government."},{"time":261212,"text":"If we're not safe, we can't be educated,"},{"time":263510,"text":"we can't be healthy,"},{"time":264858,"text":"we can't do any of the other things\nwe want to do in our lives."},{"time":267803,"text":"And we live in a country today"},{"time":269504,"text":"where we face serious criminal justice problems."},{"time":272638,"text":"We have 12 million arrests every single year."},{"time":276299,"text":"The vast majority of those arrests"},{"time":278342,"text":"are for low-level crimes, like misdemeanors,"},{"time":281354,"text":"70 to 80 percent."},{"time":283088,"text":"Less than five percent of all arrests"},{"time":285079,"text":"are for violent crime."},{"time":286974,"text":"Yet we spend 75 billion,"},{"time":289029,"text":"that's b for billion,"},{"time":290447,"text":"dollars a year on state and local corrections costs."},{"time":294574,"text":"Right now, today, we have 2.3 million people"},{"time":297415,"text":"in our jails and prisons."},{"time":299315,"text":"And we face unbelievable public safety challenges"},{"time":302111,"text":"because we have a situation"},{"time":304050,"text":"in which two thirds of the people in our jails"},{"time":306948,"text":"are there waiting for trial."},{"time":308702,"text":"They haven't yet been convicted of a crime."},{"time":310837,"text":"They're just waiting for their day in court."},{"time":312956,"text":"And 67 percent of people come back."},{"time":316504,"text":"Our recidivism rate is amongst \nthe highest in the world."},{"time":319532,"text":"Almost seven in 10 people who are released"},{"time":321635,"text":"from prison will be rearrested"},{"time":323286,"text":"in a constant cycle of crime and incarceration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327241,"text":"So when I started my job at the Arnold Foundation,"},{"time":329823,"text":"I came back to looking at a lot of these questions,"},{"time":332559,"text":"and I came back to thinking about how"},{"time":334213,"text":"we had used data and analytics to transform"},{"time":336596,"text":"the way we did criminal justice in New Jersey."},{"time":339180,"text":"And when I look at the criminal justice system"},{"time":341324,"text":"in the United States today,"},{"time":342980,"text":"I feel the exact same way that I did"},{"time":344619,"text":"about the state of New Jersey when I started there,"},{"time":347085,"text":"which is that we absolutely have to do better,"},{"time":350313,"text":"and I know that we can do better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352236,"text":"So I decided to focus"},{"time":353941,"text":"on using data and analytics"},{"time":356158,"text":"to help make the most critical decision"},{"time":358519,"text":"in public safety,"},{"time":360125,"text":"and that decision is the determination"},{"time":362146,"text":"of whether, when someone has been arrested,"},{"time":364681,"text":"whether they pose a risk to public safety"},{"time":366596,"text":"and should be detained,"},{"time":368122,"text":"or whether they don't pose a risk to public safety"},{"time":370478,"text":"and should be released."},{"time":372115,"text":"Everything that happens in criminal cases"},{"time":374034,"text":"comes out of this one decision."},{"time":375806,"text":"It impacts everything."},{"time":377302,"text":"It impacts sentencing."},{"time":378652,"text":"It impacts whether someone gets drug treatment."},{"time":380553,"text":"It impacts crime and violence."},{"time":382876,"text":"And when I talk to judges around the United States,"},{"time":384813,"text":"which I do all the time now,"},{"time":386741,"text":"they all say the same thing,"},{"time":388578,"text":"which is that we put dangerous people in jail,"},{"time":391685,"text":"and we let non-dangerous, nonviolent people out."},{"time":395210,"text":"They mean it and they believe it."},{"time":397443,"text":"But when you start to look at the data,"},{"time":399176,"text":"which, by the way, the judges don't have,"},{"time":401640,"text":"when we start to look at the data,"},{"time":403252,"text":"what we find time and time again,"},{"time":405670,"text":"is that this isn't the case."},{"time":407652,"text":"We find low-risk offenders,"},{"time":409333,"text":"which makes up 50 percent of our\nentire criminal justice population,"},{"time":413047,"text":"we find that they're in jail."},{"time":415446,"text":"Take Leslie Chew, who was a Texas man"},{"time":417932,"text":"who stole four blankets on a cold winter night."},{"time":420816,"text":"He was arrested, and he was kept in jail"},{"time":423411,"text":"on 3,500 dollars bail,"},{"time":425464,"text":"an amount that he could not afford to pay."},{"time":428240,"text":"And he stayed in jail for eight months"},{"time":430828,"text":"until his case came up for trial,"},{"time":432893,"text":"at a cost to taxpayers of more than 9,000 dollars."},{"time":436798,"text":"And at the other end of the spectrum,"},{"time":438795,"text":"we're doing an equally terrible job."},{"time":441077,"text":"The people who we find"},{"time":442649,"text":"are the highest-risk offenders,"},{"time":444668,"text":"the people who we think have the highest likelihood"},{"time":447165,"text":"of committing a new crime if they're released,"},{"time":449117,"text":"we see nationally that 50 percent of those people"},{"time":452067,"text":"are being released."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454041,"text":"The reason for this is the way we make decisions."},{"time":457215,"text":"Judges have the best intentions"},{"time":458924,"text":"when they make these decisions about risk,"},{"time":460876,"text":"but they're making them subjectively."},{"time":463360,"text":"They're like the baseball scouts 20 years ago"},{"time":465506,"text":"who were using their instinct and their experience"},{"time":467637,"text":"to try to decide what risk someone poses."},{"time":470316,"text":"They're being subjective,"},{"time":471846,"text":"and we know what happens\nwith subjective decision making,"},{"time":474906,"text":"which is that we are often wrong."},{"time":477649,"text":"What we need in this space"},{"time":479032,"text":"are strong data and analytics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481584,"text":"What I decided to look for"},{"time":483331,"text":"was a strong data and analytic risk assessment tool,"},{"time":486167,"text":"something that would let judges actually understand"},{"time":488931,"text":"with a scientific and objective way"},{"time":491190,"text":"what the risk was that was posed"},{"time":492837,"text":"by someone in front of them."},{"time":494447,"text":"I looked all over the country,"},{"time":496096,"text":"and I found that between five and 10 percent"},{"time":498038,"text":"of all U.S. jurisdictions"},{"time":499367,"text":"actually use any type of risk assessment tool,"},{"time":502345,"text":"and when I looked at these tools,"},{"time":503970,"text":"I quickly realized why."},{"time":505830,"text":"They were unbelievably expensive to administer,"},{"time":508520,"text":"they were time-consuming,"},{"time":510048,"text":"they were limited to the local jurisdiction"},{"time":512155,"text":"in which they'd been created."},{"time":513585,"text":"So basically, they couldn't be scaled"},{"time":515378,"text":"or transferred to other places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517587,"text":"So I went out and built a phenomenal team"},{"time":519824,"text":"of data scientists and researchers"},{"time":521868,"text":"and statisticians"},{"time":523494,"text":"to build a universal risk assessment tool,"},{"time":526339,"text":"so that every single judge in\nthe United States of America"},{"time":528732,"text":"can have an objective, scientific measure of risk."},{"time":533056,"text":"In the tool that we've built,"},{"time":534714,"text":"what we did was we collected 1.5 million cases"},{"time":537582,"text":"from all around the United States,"},{"time":539280,"text":"from cities, from counties,"},{"time":540924,"text":"from every single state in the country,"},{"time":542435,"text":"the federal districts."},{"time":544181,"text":"And with those 1.5 million cases,"},{"time":546370,"text":"which is the largest data set on pretrial"},{"time":548310,"text":"in the United States today,"},{"time":550115,"text":"we were able to basically find that there were"},{"time":551980,"text":"900-plus risk factors that we could look at"},{"time":555302,"text":"to try to figure out what mattered most."},{"time":558168,"text":"And we found that there were nine specific things"},{"time":560249,"text":"that mattered all across the country"},{"time":562484,"text":"and that were the most highly predictive of risk."},{"time":565461,"text":"And so we built a universal risk assessment tool."},{"time":569166,"text":"And it looks like this."},{"time":570611,"text":"As you'll see, we put some information in,"},{"time":573223,"text":"but most of it is incredibly simple,"},{"time":575236,"text":"it's easy to use,"},{"time":576668,"text":"it focuses on things like the\ndefendant's prior convictions,"},{"time":579637,"text":"whether they've been sentenced to incarceration,"},{"time":581616,"text":"whether they've engaged in violence before,"},{"time":583880,"text":"whether they've even failed to come back to court."},{"time":586273,"text":"And with this tool, we can predict three things."},{"time":588773,"text":"First, whether or not someone will commit"},{"time":590626,"text":"a new crime if they're released."},{"time":592191,"text":"Second, for the first time,"},{"time":593855,"text":"and I think this is incredibly important,"},{"time":595716,"text":"we can predict whether someone will commit"},{"time":597639,"text":"an act of violence if they're released."},{"time":599473,"text":"And that's the single most important thing"},{"time":601360,"text":"that judges say when you talk to them."},{"time":603167,"text":"And third, we can predict whether someone"},{"time":604995,"text":"will come back to court."},{"time":606985,"text":"And every single judge in the\nUnited States of America can use it,"},{"time":610018,"text":"because it's been created on a universal data set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613830,"text":"What judges see if they run the risk assessment tool"},{"time":616439,"text":"is this -- it's a dashboard."},{"time":618559,"text":"At the top, you see the New Criminal Activity Score,"},{"time":621407,"text":"six of course being the highest,"},{"time":623336,"text":"and then in the middle you\nsee, \"Elevated risk of violence.\""},{"time":625739,"text":"What that says is that this person"},{"time":627485,"text":"is someone who has an elevated risk of violence"},{"time":629545,"text":"that the judge should look twice at."},{"time":631430,"text":"And then, towards the bottom,"},{"time":632766,"text":"you see the Failure to Appear Score,"},{"time":634734,"text":"which again is the likelihood"},{"time":636126,"text":"that someone will come back to court."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639139,"text":"Now I want to say something really important."},{"time":641352,"text":"It's not that I think we should be eliminating"},{"time":644079,"text":"the judge's instinct and experience"},{"time":646323,"text":"from this process."},{"time":647927,"text":"I don't."},{"time":648985,"text":"I actually believe the problem that we see"},{"time":650992,"text":"and the reason that we have\nthese incredible system errors,"},{"time":653846,"text":"where we're incarcerating\nlow-level, nonviolent people"},{"time":656933,"text":"and we're releasing high-risk, dangerous people,"},{"time":660105,"text":"is that we don't have an objective measure of risk."},{"time":662828,"text":"But what I believe should happen"},{"time":664128,"text":"is that we should take that\ndata-driven risk assessment"},{"time":666928,"text":"and combine that with the\njudge's instinct and experience"},{"time":669969,"text":"to lead us to better decision making."},{"time":672927,"text":"The tool went statewide in Kentucky on July 1,"},{"time":676230,"text":"and we're about to go up in a\nnumber of other U.S. jurisdictions."},{"time":679581,"text":"Our goal, quite simply, is that every single judge"},{"time":682172,"text":"in the United States will use a data-driven risk tool"},{"time":684364,"text":"within the next five years."},{"time":686455,"text":"We're now working on risk tools"},{"time":687807,"text":"for prosecutors and for police officers as well,"},{"time":691091,"text":"to try to take a system that runs today"},{"time":693791,"text":"in America the same way it did 50 years ago,"},{"time":696587,"text":"based on instinct and experience,"},{"time":698684,"text":"and make it into one that runs"},{"time":700539,"text":"on data and analytics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703008,"text":"Now, the great news about all this,"},{"time":704929,"text":"and we have a ton of work left to do,"},{"time":706546,"text":"and we have a lot of culture to change,"},{"time":708403,"text":"but the great news about all of it"},{"time":710149,"text":"is that we know it works."},{"time":712017,"text":"It's why Google is Google,"},{"time":714170,"text":"and it's why all these baseball teams use moneyball"},{"time":716632,"text":"to win games."},{"time":718413,"text":"The great news for us as well"},{"time":720150,"text":"is that it's the way that we can transform"},{"time":722046,"text":"the American criminal justice system."},{"time":724367,"text":"It's how we can make our streets safer,"},{"time":726724,"text":"we can reduce our prison costs,"},{"time":729023,"text":"and we can make our system much fairer"},{"time":731090,"text":"and more just."},{"time":732815,"text":"Some people call it data science."},{"time":734977,"text":"I call it moneyballing criminal justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737278,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739082,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}